<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1877,2010]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="201" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">
Standing and slow-moving water bodies of all sizes with abundant aquatic vegetation; zoophage (both adults and larvae feed on the larvae of various aquatic organisms); univoltine; overwinters as adult. According to some authors (e.g. Papáček 
<number box="[398,458,1986,2010]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200" value="1987.0">1987</number>
), diapause is obligate. However, others (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovac" box="[962,1101,1986,2010]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200" refString="Kovac, D. (1982) Zur Uberwinterung der Wasserwanze Plea minutissima Leach (Heteroptera, Pleidae): Diapause mit Hilfe Plastronatmung. Nachrichten des Entomologischen Vereins Apollo, 3 (3), 59 - 76 [in German]." type="journal article" year="1982">
Kovac 
<number box="[1043,1101,1986,2010]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) report that overwinter torpor is induced by low temperature, and can be interrupted by upward fluctuations in temperature. The imago is longlived (up to 
<number box="[287,301,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="2.0">2</number>
years) and probably reproduces in the 
<number box="[737,750,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="2.0">2</number>
nd year (
<bibRefCitation author="Wefelscheid" box="[849,1055,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" refString="Wefelscheid, H. (1912) Uber die Biologie und Anatomie von Plea minutissima Leach. Zoologische Jahrbucher. Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tier, 32, 186." type="journal article" year="1912">
Wefelscheid 
<number box="[995,1055,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="1912.0">1912</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). West Palearctic.
</paragraph>
